Aliya Leigh Is Recognized as a Spokesperson for the GLBT Youth
&nbsp;
PHOENIX, AZ--(Marketwire - January 5, 2011) - In the interview with Echo Magazine,&nbsp;
Aliya Leigh mentions how she came out to her parents and the consequences she  suffered from them and her childhood religion. Aliya Leigh gave an interview about God and her sexuality. As a child, she was  raised a Jehovah's Witness, but knew she was gay. Knowing this, she tried to  commit suicide because she knew her sexuality was a sickness in God's eyes. For years, she denied her sexuality and tried to obey her bible principles.  During these years, she felt like a zombie walking in society. With the help  from friends, she was able to accept herself and her sexuality -- the way God  made her. Aliya Leigh is a spokesperson for teenagers who are part of the GLBT community  and tries to help them in any way she can. She knows what they are going  through and doesn't want them to suffer like she did as a teenager. The article will be featured in the January 6 edition of Echo Magazine. ### Aliya Leigh works as a producer, writer, editor and host of her own podcast entitled "Lesbian Life." The online podcast is about current affairs happening  and affecting the lesbian community globally. Aliya writes and edits film and television scripts, as well as young adult  horror, suspense and thriller novels. She is a skateboard designer for the  Puzzle Me line. Aliya Leigh owns Striving For Pi, LLC; which is a Production and Publishing  company. Striving For Pi, LLC resources will be dedicated to independent films,  web shows and graphic novels. She is a trustee of the National Writer's Union, on the Board of Directors  of AZWIT and an active member of ASCAP. Email: aliyaleigh@aliyaleigh.com Phone: (520) 405-2724

